      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/1/183/10",
      "text": [
        "أَقُولُ مَا تَسْمَعُونَ، وَاللهُ الْمُسْتَعَانُ عَلى نَفْسِي وَأَنْفُسِكُمْ، وَهُوَ حَسْبُنَا ﴿وَنِعْمَ الْوَكِيلُ﴾!"
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
          "I say what you are hearing. I seek Allāh’s help for myself and yourselves. He is enough for me and He is an excellent trustee <a href=\"/books/quran:3#h173\">[3:173]</a>."
        ]
      }
    },
